title: Google service to speed loading of news articles
text:
Photo: Josh Edelson, JOSH EDELSON / SAN FRANCISCO CHR The Google logo is seen before the start of a media event in San Francisco on Sept. 29, 2015. The Google logo is seen before the start of a media event in San...
Google formally announced a new project Wednesday, in partnership with Twitter and a broad selection of publishers, to ensure that news articles load more quickly on the Web. But one name was conspicuously absent from the presentation: Facebook. The Google logo is seen before the start of a media event in San Francisco on Sept. 29, 2015.
